<figureCitation id="C9BB00C71949C53BFEDEF92FFB6CF8B0" box="[1158,1243,1781,1803]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="19.[164,243,1834,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1413,203,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-0@19.[192,1418,195,1805]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 13. Nesocerus spp. nov. Male pygofer in lateral view (A, H, O), male subgenital plate in ventral (B, I, P) and lateral views (C, J, Q), aedeagus in lateral (D, K, R) and caudal views (E, L, S), style in lateral view (F, M, T), style and connective in dorsal view (G, N, U). A–G, Nesocerus flexus; H–N, Nesocerus breviprocessus; O–U, Nesocerus latus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440689" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440689/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="536">13H–N</figureCitation>
